body:
So today I was started a normal and was in champion select, I wanted to change my summoner last second and when I did I "lost" internet connection. Not sure if these events are connected but stating it anyway. I opened my browser and the internet was working fine but my client still said "Trying to Reconnect" so I clicked "Exit instead" and attempted to log back in. Well that's when things got bad. I typed in my username and password and pressed Enter as usual but the client got stuck on "Authenticating" After about a minute it stopped and said "Something went wrong" It gave the link to the Riot Support page. I clicked this link but for some reason the support page wouldn`t open up. I typed in the support page through Google and it also wouldn`t open up. Pretty much everything on the League of Legends website worked EXCEPT the support page. Only way I'm typing this now is because I`m using a separate computer. Anyhow, I pressed the "Full repair" button under the little settings button on the log on screen hoping that would fix things, but it didn`t, the full repair went through its course but it changed nothing, I still couldn`t log in. I can log in on the computer I'm using currently but this computer is a labtop and quite slow, not made for League of Legends gaming. I`ve tried restarting my computer and I might reinstall League of Legends on that computer. I don`t know. Please help!

{{sticker:cass-cry}}



UPDATE: Game working now, no idea why or how. Rito why you do dis lol. If someone helped thank you, if not... wat wat wat wat wat gg report team
